70// Concrete instance of RecordableEncodedFrame wrapping needed content
71// from EncodedFrame.
72class WebRtcRecordableEncodedFrame : public RecordableEncodedFrame {
73 public:
74 explicit WebRtcRecordableEncodedFrame(
75 const EncodedFrame& frame,
76 RecordableEncodedFrame::EncodedResolution resolution)
77 : buffer_(frame.GetEncodedData()),
78 render_time_ms_(frame.RenderTime()),
79 codec_(frame.CodecSpecific()->codecType),
80 is_key_frame_(frame.FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey),
81 resolution_(resolution) {
82 if (frame.ColorSpace()) {
83 color_space_ = *frame.ColorSpace();
84 }
85 }
86
87 // VideoEncodedSinkInterface::FrameBuffer
88 rtc::scoped_refptr<const EncodedImageBufferInterface> encoded_buffer()
89 const override {
90 return buffer_;
91 }
92
93 absl::optional<webrtc::ColorSpace> color_space() const override {
94 return color_space_;
95 }
96
97 VideoCodecType codec() const override { return codec_; }
98
99 bool is_key_frame() const override { return is_key_frame_; }
100
101 EncodedResolution resolution() const override { return resolution_; }
102
103 Timestamp render_time() const override {
104 return Timestamp::Millis(render_time_ms_);
105 }
106
107 private:
108 rtc::scoped_refptr<EncodedImageBufferInterface> buffer_;
109 int64_t render_time_ms_;
110 VideoCodecType codec_;
111 bool is_key_frame_;
112 EncodedResolution resolution_;
113 absl::optional<webrtc::ColorSpace> color_space_;
114};

116VideoCodec CreateDecoderVideoCodec(const VideoReceiveStream::Decoder& decoder) {
117 VideoCodec codec;
118 codec.codecType = PayloadStringToCodecType(decoder.video_format.name);
119
120 if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
121 *(codec.VP8()) = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp8Settings();
122 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
123 *(codec.VP9()) = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultVp9Settings();
124 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecH264) {
125 *(codec.H264()) = VideoEncoder::GetDefaultH264Settings();
126 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecMultiplex) {
127 VideoReceiveStream::Decoder associated_decoder = decoder;
128 associated_decoder.video_format =
129 SdpVideoFormat(CodecTypeToPayloadString(kVideoCodecVP9));
130 VideoCodec associated_codec = CreateDecoderVideoCodec(associated_decoder);
131 associated_codec.codecType = kVideoCodecMultiplex;
132 return associated_codec;
133 }
134
135 FieldTrialOptional<int> width("w");
136 FieldTrialOptional<int> height("h");
137 ParseFieldTrial(
138 {&width, &height},
139 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-Video-InitialDecoderResolution"));
140 if (width && height) {
141 codec.width = width.Value();
142 codec.height = height.Value();
143 } else {
144 codec.width = 320;
145 codec.height = 180;
146 }
147
148 const int kDefaultStartBitrate = 300;
149 codec.startBitrate = codec.minBitrate = codec.maxBitrate =
150 kDefaultStartBitrate;
151
152 return codec;
153}

155// Video decoder class to be used for unknown codecs. Doesn't support decoding
156// but logs messages to LS_ERROR.
157class NullVideoDecoder : public webrtc::VideoDecoder {
158 public:
159 int32_t InitDecode(const webrtc::VideoCodec* codec_settings,
160 int32_t number_of_cores) override {
161 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Can't initialize NullVideoDecoder.";
162 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
163 }
164
165 int32_t Decode(const webrtc::EncodedImage& input_image,
166 bool missing_frames,
167 int64_t render_time_ms) override {
168 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "The NullVideoDecoder doesn't support decoding.";
169 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
170 }
171
172 int32_t RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(
173 webrtc::DecodedImageCallback* callback) override {
174 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
175 << "Can't register decode complete callback on NullVideoDecoder.";
176 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
177 }
178
179 int32_t Release() override { return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK; }
180
181 const char* ImplementationName() const override { return "NullVideoDecoder"; }
182};

184bool IsKeyFrameAndUnspecifiedResolution(const EncodedFrame& frame) {
185 return frame.FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey &&
186 frame.EncodedImage()._encodedWidth == 0 &&
187 frame.EncodedImage()._encodedHeight == 0;
188}
189
190// TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/9974): Consider removing this workaround.
191// Maximum time between frames before resetting the FrameBuffer to avoid RTP
192// timestamps wraparound to affect FrameBuffer.
193constexpr int kInactiveStreamThresholdMs = 600000; // 10 minutes.

195} // namespace

197int DetermineMaxWaitForFrame(const VideoReceiveStream::Config& config,
198 bool is_keyframe) {
199 // A (arbitrary) conversion factor between the remotely signalled NACK buffer
200 // time (if not present defaults to 1000ms) and the maximum time we wait for a
201 // remote frame. Chosen to not change existing defaults when using not
202 // rtx-time.
203 const int conversion_factor = 3;
204
205 if (config.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms > 0 &&
206 conversion_factor * config.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms < kMaxWaitForFrameMs) {
207 return is_keyframe ? config.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms
208 : conversion_factor * config.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms;
209 }
210 return is_keyframe ? VideoReceiveStream2::kMaxWaitForKeyFrameMs
211 : kMaxWaitForFrameMs;
212}

214VideoReceiveStream2::VideoReceiveStream2(
215 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
216 TaskQueueBase* current_queue,
217 RtpStreamReceiverControllerInterface* receiver_controller,
218 int num_cpu_cores,
219 PacketRouter* packet_router,
220 VideoReceiveStream::Config config,
221 ProcessThread* process_thread,
222 CallStats* call_stats,
223 Clock* clock,
224 VCMTiming* timing)
225 : task_queue_factory_(task_queue_factory),
226 transport_adapter_(config.rtcp_send_transport),
227 config_(std::move(config)),
228 num_cpu_cores_(num_cpu_cores),
229 worker_thread_(current_queue),
230 clock_(clock),
231 call_stats_(call_stats),
232 source_tracker_(clock_),
233 stats_proxy_(&config_, clock_, worker_thread_),
234 rtp_receive_statistics_(ReceiveStatistics::Create(clock_)),
235 timing_(timing),
236 video_receiver_(clock_, timing_.get()),
237 rtp_video_stream_receiver_(worker_thread_,
238 clock_,
239 &transport_adapter_,
240 call_stats->AsRtcpRttStats(),
241 packet_router,
242 &config_,
243 rtp_receive_statistics_.get(),
244 &stats_proxy_,
245 &stats_proxy_,
246 process_thread,
247 this, // NackSender
248 nullptr, // Use default KeyFrameRequestSender
249 this, // OnCompleteFrameCallback
250 config_.frame_decryptor,
251 config_.frame_transformer),
252 rtp_stream_sync_(current_queue, this),
253 max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_(DetermineMaxWaitForFrame(config, true)),
254 max_wait_for_frame_ms_(DetermineMaxWaitForFrame(config, false)),
255 low_latency_renderer_enabled_("enabled", true),
256 low_latency_renderer_include_predecode_buffer_("include_predecode_buffer",
257 true),
258 maximum_pre_stream_decoders_("max", kDefaultMaximumPreStreamDecoders),
259 decode_queue_(task_queue_factory_->CreateTaskQueue(
260 "DecodingQueue",
261 TaskQueueFactory::Priority::HIGH)) {
262 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "VideoReceiveStream2: " << config_.ToString();
263
264 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread_);
265 RTC_DCHECK(config_.renderer);
266 RTC_DCHECK(call_stats_);
267 module_process_sequence_checker_.Detach();
268
269 RTC_DCHECK(!config_.decoders.empty());
270 RTC_CHECK(config_.decoder_factory);
271 std::set<int> decoder_payload_types;
272 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders) {
273 RTC_CHECK(decoder_payload_types.find(decoder.payload_type) ==
274 decoder_payload_types.end())
275 << "Duplicate payload type (" << decoder.payload_type
276 << ") for different decoders.";
277 decoder_payload_types.insert(decoder.payload_type);
278 }
279
280 timing_->set_render_delay(config_.render_delay_ms);
281
282 frame_buffer_.reset(
283 new video_coding::FrameBuffer(clock_, timing_.get(), &stats_proxy_));
284
285 // Register with RtpStreamReceiverController.
286 media_receiver_ = receiver_controller->CreateReceiver(
287 config_.rtp.remote_ssrc, &rtp_video_stream_receiver_);
288 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
289 rtx_receive_stream_ = std::make_unique<RtxReceiveStream>(
290 &rtp_video_stream_receiver_, config.rtp.rtx_associated_payload_types,
291 config_.rtp.remote_ssrc, rtp_receive_statistics_.get());
292 rtx_receiver_ = receiver_controller->CreateReceiver(
293 config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc, rtx_receive_stream_.get());
294 } else {
295 rtp_receive_statistics_->EnableRetransmitDetection(config.rtp.remote_ssrc,
296 true);
297 }
298
299 ParseFieldTrial({&low_latency_renderer_enabled_,
300 &low_latency_renderer_include_predecode_buffer_},
301 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-LowLatencyRenderer"));
302 ParseFieldTrial(
303 {
304 &maximum_pre_stream_decoders_,
305 },
306 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-PreStreamDecoders"));
307}

309VideoReceiveStream2::~VideoReceiveStream2() {
310 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
311 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "~VideoReceiveStream2: " << config_.ToString();
312 Stop();
313}

329void VideoReceiveStream2::Start() {
330 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
331
332 if (decoder_running_) {
333 return;
334 }
335
336 const bool protected_by_fec = config_.rtp.protected_by_flexfec ||
337 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.IsUlpfecEnabled();
338
339 if (rtp_video_stream_receiver_.IsRetransmissionsEnabled() &&
340 protected_by_fec) {
341 frame_buffer_->SetProtectionMode(kProtectionNackFEC);
342 }
343
344 transport_adapter_.Enable();
345 rtc::VideoSinkInterface<VideoFrame>* renderer = nullptr;
346 if (config_.enable_prerenderer_smoothing) {
347 incoming_video_stream_.reset(new IncomingVideoStream(
348 task_queue_factory_, config_.render_delay_ms, this));
349 renderer = incoming_video_stream_.get();
350 } else {
351 renderer = this;
352 }
353
354 int decoders_count = 0;
355 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders) {
356 // Create up to maximum_pre_stream_decoders_ up front, wait the the other
357 // decoders until they are requested (i.e., we receive the corresponding
358 // payload).
359 if (decoders_count < maximum_pre_stream_decoders_) {
360 CreateAndRegisterExternalDecoder(decoder);
361 ++decoders_count;
362 }
363
364 VideoCodec codec = CreateDecoderVideoCodec(decoder);
365
366 const bool raw_payload =
367 config_.rtp.raw_payload_types.count(decoder.payload_type) > 0;
368 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.AddReceiveCodec(decoder.payload_type, codec,
369 decoder.video_format.parameters,
370 raw_payload);
371 RTC_CHECK_EQ(VCM_OK, video_receiver_.RegisterReceiveCodec(
372 decoder.payload_type, &codec, num_cpu_cores_));
373 }
374
375 RTC_DCHECK(renderer != nullptr);
376 video_stream_decoder_.reset(
377 new VideoStreamDecoder(&video_receiver_, &stats_proxy_, renderer));
378
379 // Make sure we register as a stats observer *after* we've prepared the
380 // |video_stream_decoder_|.
381 call_stats_->RegisterStatsObserver(this);
382
383 // Start decoding on task queue.
384 video_receiver_.DecoderThreadStarting();
385 stats_proxy_.DecoderThreadStarting();
386 decode_queue_.PostTask([this] {
387 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
388 decoder_stopped_ = false;
389 StartNextDecode();
390 });
391 decoder_running_ = true;
392 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.StartReceive();
393}
394
395void VideoReceiveStream2::Stop() {
396 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
397 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.StopReceive();
398
399 stats_proxy_.OnUniqueFramesCounted(
400 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.GetUniqueFramesSeen());
401
402 decode_queue_.PostTask([this] { frame_buffer_->Stop(); });
403
404 call_stats_->DeregisterStatsObserver(this);
405
406 if (decoder_running_) {
407 rtc::Event done;
408 decode_queue_.PostTask([this, &done] {
409 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
410 decoder_stopped_ = true;
411 done.Set();
412 });
413 done.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
414
415 decoder_running_ = false;
416 video_receiver_.DecoderThreadStopped();
417 stats_proxy_.DecoderThreadStopped();
418 // Deregister external decoders so they are no longer running during
419 // destruction. This effectively stops the VCM since the decoder thread is
420 // stopped, the VCM is deregistered and no asynchronous decoder threads are
421 // running.
422 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders)
423 video_receiver_.RegisterExternalDecoder(nullptr, decoder.payload_type);
424
425 UpdateHistograms();
426 }
427
428 video_stream_decoder_.reset();
429 incoming_video_stream_.reset();
430 transport_adapter_.Disable();
431}
432
433void VideoReceiveStream2::CreateAndRegisterExternalDecoder(
434 const Decoder& decoder) {
435 std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> video_decoder =
436 config_.decoder_factory->CreateVideoDecoder(decoder.video_format);
437 // If we still have no valid decoder, we have to create a "Null" decoder
438 // that ignores all calls. The reason we can get into this state is that the
439 // old decoder factory interface doesn't have a way to query supported
440 // codecs.
441 if (!video_decoder) {
442 video_decoder = std::make_unique<NullVideoDecoder>();
443 }
444
445 std::string decoded_output_file =
446 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-DecoderDataDumpDirectory");
447 // Because '/' can't be used inside a field trial parameter, we use ';'
448 // instead.
449 // This is only relevant to WebRTC-DecoderDataDumpDirectory
450 // field trial. ';' is chosen arbitrary. Even though it's a legal character
451 // in some file systems, we can sacrifice ability to use it in the path to
452 // dumped video, since it's developers-only feature for debugging.
453 absl::c_replace(decoded_output_file, ';', '/');
454 if (!decoded_output_file.empty()) {
455 char filename_buffer[256];
456 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder ssb(filename_buffer);
457 ssb << decoded_output_file << "/webrtc_receive_stream_"
458 << this->config_.rtp.remote_ssrc << "-" << rtc::TimeMicros() << ".ivf";
459 video_decoder = CreateFrameDumpingDecoderWrapper(
460 std::move(video_decoder), FileWrapper::OpenWriteOnly(ssb.str()));
461 }
462
463 video_decoders_.push_back(std::move(video_decoder));
464 video_receiver_.RegisterExternalDecoder(video_decoders_.back().get(),
465 decoder.payload_type);
466}

468VideoReceiveStream::Stats VideoReceiveStream2::GetStats() const {
469 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
470 VideoReceiveStream2::Stats stats = stats_proxy_.GetStats();
471 stats.total_bitrate_bps = 0;
472 StreamStatistician* statistician =
473 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(stats.ssrc);
474 if (statistician) {
475 stats.rtp_stats = statistician->GetStats();
476 stats.total_bitrate_bps = statistician->BitrateReceived();
477 }
478 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
479 StreamStatistician* rtx_statistician =
480 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc);
481 if (rtx_statistician)
482 stats.total_bitrate_bps += rtx_statistician->BitrateReceived();
483 }
484 return stats;
485}

487void VideoReceiveStream2::UpdateHistograms() {
488 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
489 absl::optional<int> fraction_lost;
490 StreamDataCounters rtp_stats;
491 StreamStatistician* statistician =
492 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(config_.rtp.remote_ssrc);
493 if (statistician) {
494 fraction_lost = statistician->GetFractionLostInPercent();
495 rtp_stats = statistician->GetReceiveStreamDataCounters();
496 }
497 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
498 StreamStatistician* rtx_statistician =
499 rtp_receive_statistics_->GetStatistician(config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc);
500 if (rtx_statistician) {
501 StreamDataCounters rtx_stats =
502 rtx_statistician->GetReceiveStreamDataCounters();
503 stats_proxy_.UpdateHistograms(fraction_lost, rtp_stats, &rtx_stats);
504 return;
505 }
506 }
507 stats_proxy_.UpdateHistograms(fraction_lost, rtp_stats, nullptr);
508}

510bool VideoReceiveStream2::SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(int delay_ms) {
511 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
512 if (delay_ms < kMinBaseMinimumDelayMs || delay_ms > kMaxBaseMinimumDelayMs) {
513 return false;
514 }
515
516 base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ = delay_ms;
517 UpdatePlayoutDelays();
518 return true;
519}
520
521int VideoReceiveStream2::GetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs() const {
522 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
523 return base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_;
524}
525
526void VideoReceiveStream2::OnFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame) {
527 VideoFrameMetaData frame_meta(video_frame, clock_->CurrentTime());
528
529 worker_thread_->PostTask(
530 ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, [frame_meta, this]() {
531 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
532 int64_t video_playout_ntp_ms;
533 int64_t sync_offset_ms;
534 double estimated_freq_khz;
535 if (rtp_stream_sync_.GetStreamSyncOffsetInMs(
536 frame_meta.rtp_timestamp, frame_meta.render_time_ms(),
537 &video_playout_ntp_ms, &sync_offset_ms, &estimated_freq_khz)) {
538 stats_proxy_.OnSyncOffsetUpdated(video_playout_ntp_ms, sync_offset_ms,
539 estimated_freq_khz);
540 }
541 stats_proxy_.OnRenderedFrame(frame_meta);
542 }));
543
544 source_tracker_.OnFrameDelivered(video_frame.packet_infos());
545 config_.renderer->OnFrame(video_frame);
546 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&pending_resolution_mutex_);
547 if (pending_resolution_.has_value()) {
548 if (!pending_resolution_->empty() &&
549 (video_frame.width() != static_cast<int>(pending_resolution_->width) ||
550 video_frame.height() !=
551 static_cast<int>(pending_resolution_->height))) {
552 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
553 << "Recordable encoded frame stream resolution was reported as "
554 << pending_resolution_->width << "x" << pending_resolution_->height
555 << " but the stream is now " << video_frame.width()
556 << video_frame.height();
557 }
558 pending_resolution_ = RecordableEncodedFrame::EncodedResolution{
559 static_cast<unsigned>(video_frame.width()),
560 static_cast<unsigned>(video_frame.height())};
561 }
562}

583void VideoReceiveStream2::RequestKeyFrame(int64_t timestamp_ms) {
584 // Running on worker_sequence_checker_.
585 // Called from RtpVideoStreamReceiver (rtp_video_stream_receiver_ is
586 // ultimately responsible).
587 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.RequestKeyFrame();
588 decode_queue_.PostTask([this, timestamp_ms]() {
589 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
590 last_keyframe_request_ms_ = timestamp_ms;
591 });
592}
593
594void VideoReceiveStream2::OnCompleteFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
595 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
596
597 // TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/9974): Consider removing this workaround.
598 int64_t time_now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
599 if (last_complete_frame_time_ms_ > 0 &&
600 time_now_ms - last_complete_frame_time_ms_ > kInactiveStreamThresholdMs) {
601 frame_buffer_->Clear();
602 }
603 last_complete_frame_time_ms_ = time_now_ms;
604
605 const VideoPlayoutDelay& playout_delay = frame->EncodedImage().playout_delay_;
606 if (playout_delay.min_ms >= 0) {
607 frame_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ = playout_delay.min_ms;
608 UpdatePlayoutDelays();
609 }
610
611 if (playout_delay.max_ms >= 0) {
612 frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_ = playout_delay.max_ms;
613 UpdatePlayoutDelays();
614 }
615
616 int64_t last_continuous_pid = frame_buffer_->InsertFrame(std::move(frame));
617 if (last_continuous_pid != -1)
618 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.FrameContinuous(last_continuous_pid);
619}

621void VideoReceiveStream2::OnRttUpdate(int64_t avg_rtt_ms, int64_t max_rtt_ms) {
622 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
623 frame_buffer_->UpdateRtt(max_rtt_ms);
624 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.UpdateRtt(max_rtt_ms);
625 stats_proxy_.OnRttUpdate(avg_rtt_ms);
626}

633absl::optional<Syncable::Info> VideoReceiveStream2::GetInfo() const {
634 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
635 absl::optional<Syncable::Info> info =
636 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.GetSyncInfo();
637
638 if (!info)
639 return absl::nullopt;
640
641 info->current_delay_ms = timing_->TargetVideoDelay();
642 return info;
643}

664int64_t VideoReceiveStream2::GetMaxWaitMs() const {
665 return keyframe_required_ ? max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_
666 : max_wait_for_frame_ms_;
667}
668
669void VideoReceiveStream2::StartNextDecode() {
670 // Running on the decode thread.
671 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VideoReceiveStream2::StartNextDecode");
672 frame_buffer_->NextFrame(
673 GetMaxWaitMs(), keyframe_required_, &decode_queue_,
674 /* encoded frame handler */
675 [this](std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame, ReturnReason res) {
676 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame == nullptr, res == ReturnReason::kTimeout);
677 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame != nullptr, res == ReturnReason::kFrameFound);
678 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
679 if (decoder_stopped_)
680 return;
681 if (frame) {
682 HandleEncodedFrame(std::move(frame));
683 } else {
684 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
685 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
686 task_safety_, [this, now_ms, wait_ms = GetMaxWaitMs()]() {
687 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
688 HandleFrameBufferTimeout(now_ms, wait_ms);
689 }));
690 }
691 StartNextDecode();
692 });
693}
694
695void VideoReceiveStream2::HandleEncodedFrame(
696 std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
697 // Running on |decode_queue_|.
698 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
699
700 // Current OnPreDecode only cares about QP for VP8.
701 int qp = -1;
702 if (frame->CodecSpecific()->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
703 if (!vp8::GetQp(frame->data(), frame->size(), &qp)) {
704 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to extract QP from VP8 video frame";
705 }
706 }
707 stats_proxy_.OnPreDecode(frame->CodecSpecific()->codecType, qp);
708
709 bool force_request_key_frame = false;
710 int64_t decoded_frame_picture_id = -1;
711
712 const bool keyframe_request_is_due =
713 now_ms >= (last_keyframe_request_ms_ + max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_);
714
715 if (!video_receiver_.IsExternalDecoderRegistered(frame->PayloadType())) {
716 // Look for the decoder with this payload type.
717 for (const Decoder& decoder : config_.decoders) {
718 if (decoder.payload_type == frame->PayloadType()) {
719 CreateAndRegisterExternalDecoder(decoder);
720 break;
721 }
722 }
723 }
724
725 int64_t frame_id = frame->Id();
726 bool received_frame_is_keyframe =
727 frame->FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
728 int decode_result = DecodeAndMaybeDispatchEncodedFrame(std::move(frame));
729 if (decode_result == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK ||
730 decode_result == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK_REQUEST_KEYFRAME) {
731 keyframe_required_ = false;
732 frame_decoded_ = true;
733
734 decoded_frame_picture_id = frame_id;
735
736 if (decode_result == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK_REQUEST_KEYFRAME)
737 force_request_key_frame = true;
738 } else if (!frame_decoded_ || !keyframe_required_ ||
739 keyframe_request_is_due) {
740 keyframe_required_ = true;
741 // TODO(philipel): Remove this keyframe request when downstream project
742 // has been fixed.
743 force_request_key_frame = true;
744 }
745
746 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
747 task_safety_,
748 [this, now_ms, received_frame_is_keyframe, force_request_key_frame,
749 decoded_frame_picture_id, keyframe_request_is_due]() {
750 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
751
752 if (decoded_frame_picture_id != -1)
753 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.FrameDecoded(decoded_frame_picture_id);
754
755 HandleKeyFrameGeneration(received_frame_is_keyframe, now_ms,
756 force_request_key_frame,
757 keyframe_request_is_due);
758 }));
759}
760
761int VideoReceiveStream2::DecodeAndMaybeDispatchEncodedFrame(
762 std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
763 // Running on decode_queue_.
764
765 // If |buffered_encoded_frames_| grows out of control (=60 queued frames),
766 // maybe due to a stuck decoder, we just halt the process here and log the
767 // error.
768 const bool encoded_frame_output_enabled =
769 encoded_frame_buffer_function_ != nullptr &&
770 buffered_encoded_frames_.size() < kBufferedEncodedFramesMaxSize;
771 EncodedFrame* frame_ptr = frame.get();
772 if (encoded_frame_output_enabled) {
773 // If we receive a key frame with unset resolution, hold on dispatching the
774 // frame and following ones until we know a resolution of the stream.
775 // NOTE: The code below has a race where it can report the wrong
776 // resolution for keyframes after an initial keyframe of other resolution.
777 // However, the only known consumer of this information is the W3C
778 // MediaRecorder and it will only use the resolution in the first encoded
779 // keyframe from WebRTC, so misreporting is fine.
780 buffered_encoded_frames_.push_back(std::move(frame));
781 if (buffered_encoded_frames_.size() == kBufferedEncodedFramesMaxSize)
782 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "About to halt recordable encoded frame output due "
783 "to too many buffered frames.";
784
785 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&pending_resolution_mutex_);
786 if (IsKeyFrameAndUnspecifiedResolution(*frame_ptr) &&
787 !pending_resolution_.has_value())
788 pending_resolution_.emplace();
789 }
790
791 int decode_result = video_receiver_.Decode(frame_ptr);
792 if (encoded_frame_output_enabled) {
793 absl::optional<RecordableEncodedFrame::EncodedResolution>
794 pending_resolution;
795 {
796 // Fish out |pending_resolution_| to avoid taking the mutex on every lap
797 // or dispatching under the mutex in the flush loop.
798 webrtc::MutexLock lock(&pending_resolution_mutex_);
799 if (pending_resolution_.has_value())
800 pending_resolution = *pending_resolution_;
801 }
802 if (!pending_resolution.has_value() || !pending_resolution->empty()) {
803 // Flush the buffered frames.
804 for (const auto& frame : buffered_encoded_frames_) {
805 RecordableEncodedFrame::EncodedResolution resolution{
806 frame->EncodedImage()._encodedWidth,
807 frame->EncodedImage()._encodedHeight};
808 if (IsKeyFrameAndUnspecifiedResolution(*frame)) {
809 RTC_DCHECK(!pending_resolution->empty());
810 resolution = *pending_resolution;
811 }
812 encoded_frame_buffer_function_(
813 WebRtcRecordableEncodedFrame(*frame, resolution));
814 }
815 buffered_encoded_frames_.clear();
816 }
817 }
818 return decode_result;
819}
820
821void VideoReceiveStream2::HandleKeyFrameGeneration(
822 bool received_frame_is_keyframe,
823 int64_t now_ms,
824 bool always_request_key_frame,
825 bool keyframe_request_is_due) {
826 // Running on worker_sequence_checker_.
827
828 bool request_key_frame = always_request_key_frame;
829
830 // Repeat sending keyframe requests if we've requested a keyframe.
831 if (keyframe_generation_requested_) {
832 if (received_frame_is_keyframe) {
833 keyframe_generation_requested_ = false;
834 } else if (keyframe_request_is_due) {
835 if (!IsReceivingKeyFrame(now_ms)) {
836 request_key_frame = true;
837 }
838 } else {
839 // It hasn't been long enough since the last keyframe request, do nothing.
840 }
841 }
842
843 if (request_key_frame) {
844 // HandleKeyFrameGeneration is initated from the decode thread -
845 // RequestKeyFrame() triggers a call back to the decode thread.
846 // Perhaps there's a way to avoid that.
847 RequestKeyFrame(now_ms);
848 }
849}
850
851void VideoReceiveStream2::HandleFrameBufferTimeout(int64_t now_ms,
852 int64_t wait_ms) {
853 // Running on |worker_sequence_checker_|.
854 absl::optional<int64_t> last_packet_ms =
855 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.LastReceivedPacketMs();
856
857 // To avoid spamming keyframe requests for a stream that is not active we
858 // check if we have received a packet within the last 5 seconds.
859 const bool stream_is_active =
860 last_packet_ms && now_ms - *last_packet_ms < 5000;
861 if (!stream_is_active)
862 stats_proxy_.OnStreamInactive();
863
864 if (stream_is_active && !IsReceivingKeyFrame(now_ms) &&
865 (!config_.crypto_options.sframe.require_frame_encryption ||
866 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.IsDecryptable())) {
867 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "No decodable frame in " << wait_ms
868 << " ms, requesting keyframe.";
869 RequestKeyFrame(now_ms);
870 }
871}
872
873bool VideoReceiveStream2::IsReceivingKeyFrame(int64_t timestamp_ms) const {
874 // Running on worker_sequence_checker_.
875 absl::optional<int64_t> last_keyframe_packet_ms =
876 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.LastReceivedKeyframePacketMs();
877
878 // If we recently have been receiving packets belonging to a keyframe then
879 // we assume a keyframe is currently being received.
880 bool receiving_keyframe =
881 last_keyframe_packet_ms &&
882 timestamp_ms - *last_keyframe_packet_ms < max_wait_for_keyframe_ms_;
883 return receiving_keyframe;
884}
885
886void VideoReceiveStream2::UpdatePlayoutDelays() const {
887 // Running on worker_sequence_checker_.
888 const int minimum_delay_ms =
889 std::max({frame_minimum_playout_delay_ms_, base_minimum_playout_delay_ms_,
890 syncable_minimum_playout_delay_ms_});
891 if (minimum_delay_ms >= 0) {
892 timing_->set_min_playout_delay(minimum_delay_ms);
893 if (frame_minimum_playout_delay_ms_ == 0 &&
894 frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_ > 0 && low_latency_renderer_enabled_) {
895 // TODO(kron): Estimate frame rate from video stream.
896 constexpr double kFrameRate = 60.0;
897 // Convert playout delay in ms to number of frames.
898 int max_composition_delay_in_frames = std::lrint(
899 static_cast<double>(frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_ * kFrameRate) /
900 rtc::kNumMillisecsPerSec);
901 if (low_latency_renderer_include_predecode_buffer_) {
902 // Subtract frames in buffer.
903 max_composition_delay_in_frames = std::max<int16_t>(
904 max_composition_delay_in_frames - frame_buffer_->Size(), 0);
905 }
906 timing_->SetMaxCompositionDelayInFrames(
907 absl::make_optional(max_composition_delay_in_frames));
908 }
909 }
910
911 const int maximum_delay_ms = frame_maximum_playout_delay_ms_;
912 if (maximum_delay_ms >= 0) {
913 timing_->set_max_playout_delay(maximum_delay_ms);
914 }
915}

917std::vector<webrtc::RtpSource> VideoReceiveStream2::GetSources() const {
918 return source_tracker_.GetSources();
919}
920
921VideoReceiveStream2::RecordingState
922VideoReceiveStream2::SetAndGetRecordingState(RecordingState state,
923 bool generate_key_frame) {
924 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
925 rtc::Event event;
926
927 // Save old state, set the new state.
928 RecordingState old_state;
929
930 decode_queue_.PostTask(
931 [this, &event, &old_state, callback = std::move(state.callback),
932 generate_key_frame,
933 last_keyframe_request = state.last_keyframe_request_ms.value_or(0)] {
934 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decode_queue_);
935 old_state.callback = std::move(encoded_frame_buffer_function_);
936 encoded_frame_buffer_function_ = std::move(callback);
937
938 old_state.last_keyframe_request_ms = last_keyframe_request_ms_;
939 last_keyframe_request_ms_ = generate_key_frame
940 ? clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()
941 : last_keyframe_request;
942
943 event.Set();
944 });
945
946 old_state.keyframe_needed = keyframe_generation_requested_;
947
948 if (generate_key_frame) {
949 rtp_video_stream_receiver_.RequestKeyFrame();
950 keyframe_generation_requested_ = true;
951 } else {
952 keyframe_generation_requested_ = state.keyframe_needed;
953 }
954
955 event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
956 return old_state;
957}
958
959void VideoReceiveStream2::GenerateKeyFrame() {
960 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_sequence_checker_);
961 RequestKeyFrame(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
962 keyframe_generation_requested_ = true;
963}
